<!DOCTYPE html><html ⚡ lang="en"><head> <% include ../../_partials/amp/_amp-head.ejs %><script async custom-element="amp-sidebar" src="https://cdn.ampproject.org/v0/amp-sidebar-0.1.js"></script><script async custom-element="amp-accordion" src="https://cdn.ampproject.org/v0/amp-accordion-0.1.js"></script><script async custom-element="amp-form" src="https://cdn.ampproject.org/v0/amp-form-0.1.js"></script><script async custom-element="amp-lightbox" src="https://cdn.ampproject.org/v0/amp-lightbox-0.1.js"></script></head><body class="home"><amp-sidebar id='sidebar' side='right' layout='nodisplay'> <% include ../../_partials/amp/_ampLandingSidebar.ejs %></amp-sidebar><header class="header fixed"> <% include ../../_partials/amp/_amp-header.ejs %></header><div class="wrap mobile-down"><div class="content"><section class="hero webUI"><div class="container"><div class="row"><div class="six columns"><div class="intro-container"><h1>SMTP Server Overlay</h1><p class="intro"> Simply use the <strong>INSTAR Preset</strong> if you don´t know the SMTP information of your Email provider. Choose the preset from the drop down menu and confirm. The Email recipient can be set in the <a href="/Web_User_Interface/720p_Series/Alarm/Email/">Email Menu</a>. Set-up this way, your camera will use an INSTAR Server to send alarm mails to your personal Email address. This transfer will be TLS encrypted and INSTAR does not store any copies of your Emails. Remember Daylight-Saving-Time!</p></div></div></div></div></section></div></div><div class="wrap"><div class="container main"> <% include ../../_partials/content/_bluenav-general.ejs %><article class="blade wrapper content"><div class="post-title"><h2>Set a Server the outgoing Alarm Emails</h2></div><div class="margin"><div><amp-img on="tap:lightbox1" role="button" tabindex="0" src="/images/720p_webUI/WebUI-Alarm_SMTP.png" width="716" height="746" layout="responsive" class="shadow"></amp-img></div></div><div class="margin"><table><tr><td width="20%"> <strong>SMTP Presets</strong></td><td>Your INSTAR camera can work with almost all email provider. The preset menu just gives you an overview over the most common outgoing email server. If you cannot find yours, simply type in your information manually below. If you don´t know your provider's server address, simply choose the <strong>INSTAR SMTP Server</strong>. This preset allows you to send your emails through an INSTAR server directly to your personal email address. All you have to do next, is to type in your personal email address as receiver in the <a href="/Web_User_Interface/720p_Series/Alarm/Email/">Email Menu</a>.</td></tr><tr><td width="20%"> <strong>SMTP Server</strong></td><td>Type in the server address of your email provider. If you don´t know the address, simply choose the INSTAR preset (above). Afterwards you just have to type in your personal email address as receiver in the <a href="/Web_User_Interface/720p_Series/Alarm/Email/">Email Menu</a>.</td></tr><tr><td width="20%"> <strong>SMTP Port</strong></td><td>Choose the port that your SMTP server uses to receive your emails. The default value for an unencrypted mail transfer (SMTP SSL: none) is <strong>25</strong>, for SSL choose port <strong>465</strong> and TLS/STARTTLS uses the port <strong>587</strong>.</td></tr><tr><td width="20%"> <strong>SMTP SSL</strong></td><td>Choose the type of encryption that your SMTP server uses. Be aware that most servers offer all types of encryption - but they all use different ports.</td></tr><tr><td width="20%"> <strong>SMTP Username</strong></td><td>Type in your email username - this is, in most cases, simply the email address that you want to use.</td></tr><tr><td width="20%"> <strong>SMTP Password</strong></td><td>Type in the password for your email account and confirm it.</td></tr></table></div><div class="dangercard"><p><strong><u>Remark:</u></strong><br/><br/>Be aware that maximum length for the email password is 39 characters. The following special characters are not supported: <span class="code">&amp; = " ` + \</span></p></div><div class="margin"><h3>Server Presets</h3><p>Simply use the <strong>INSTAR Preset</strong> if you don´t know the SMTP information of your Email provider. Choose the preset from the drop down menu and confirm. The Email recipient can be set in the <a href="/Web_User_Interface/720p_Series/Alarm/Email/">Email Menu</a>. Set-up this way, your camera will use an INSTAR Server to send alarm mails to your personal Email address. This transfer will be TLS encrypted and INSTAR does not store any copies of your Emails!</p></div></article> <!-- #################### Lightboxes ######################## --><amp-lightbox id="lightbox1" layout="nodisplay"><div class="lightbox" on="tap:lightbox1.close" role="button" tabindex="0" class="centered"><amp-img on="tap:lightbox1.close" role="button" tabindex="0" src="/images/720p_webUI/WebUI-Alarm_SMTP.png" width="716" height="746" layout="responsive" class="shadow"></amp-img></div></amp-lightbox></div></div> <% include ../../_partials/content/_bluenav-general-mobile.ejs %><footer> <% include ../../_partials/amp/_amp-footer.ejs %></footer></body></html>